title: Mine
lyrics:
[Verse 1]
You were in college, working part-time, waiting tables
Left a small town and never looked back
I was a flight risk, with a fear of falling
Wondering why we bother with love, if it never lasts

[Pre-Chorus 1]
I say, "Can you believe it?"
As we are lying on the couch
The moment, I could see it
Yes, yes, I can see it now

[Chorus]
Do you remember, we were sitting there, by the water?
You put your arm around me for the first time
You made a rebel of a careless man's careful daughter
You are the best thing that has ever been mine

[Verse 2]
Flash forward, and we are taking on the world together
And there has a drawer of my things at your place
You learn my secrets and you figure out why I am guarded
You say we will never make my parents' mistakes
[Pre-Chorus 2]
But we got bills to pay
We got nothing figured out
When it was hard to take
Yes, yes
This is what I thought about:

[Chorus]
Do you remember, we were sitting there, by the water?
You put your arm around me for the first time
You made a rebel of a careless man's careful daughter
You are the best thing that has ever been mine
Do you remember all the city lights on the water?
You saw me start to believe for the first time
You made a rebel of a careless man's careful daughter
You are the best thing that has ever been mine

[Bridge]
And I remember that fight, 2:30 A.M
As everything was slipping right out of our hands
I ran out, crying, and you followed me out into the street
Braced myself for the goodbye
'Cause that has all I have ever known
Then, you took me by surprise
You said, "I shall never leave you alone."
[Chorus 2]
You said, "I remember how we felt, sitting by the water
And every time I look at you, it has like the first time
I fell in love with a careless man's careful daughter
She is the best thing that has ever been mine"
Hold on, make it last
Hold on, never turn back
You made a rebel of a careless man's careful daughter
You are the best thing that has ever been mine

[Outro]
Yeah, yeah
Do you believe it? (Hold on)
We're gonna make it now (Hold on)
And I can see it
Yeah, yeah
I can see it now (See it now)

title: Back to December
lyrics:
[Verse 1]
I am so glad you made time to see me
How's life? Tell me, how has your family?
I have not seen them in a while
You've been good, busier than ever
We small talk, work and the weather
Your guard is up and I know why

[Pre-Chorus]
Because the last time you saw me
Is still burned in the back of your mind
You gave me roses, and I left them there to die

[Chorus]
So this is me swallowing my pride
Standing in front of you, saying I am sorry for that night
And I go back to December all the time
It turns out freedom am not nothing but missing you
Wishing I had realized what I had when you were mine
I had go back to December, turn around and make it alright
I go back to December all the time
[Verse 2]
These days, I have not been sleeping
Staying up, playing back myself leaving
When your birthday passed and I did not call
And I think about summer, all the beautiful times
I watched you laughing from the passenger side and
Realized I loved you in the fall

[Pre-Chorus]
And then the cold came
The dark days when fear crept into my mind
You gave me all your love, and all I gave you was goodbye

[Chorus]
So this is me swallowing my pride
Standing in front of you, saying I am sorry for that night
And I go back to December all the time
It turns out freedom am not nothing but missing you
Wishing I had realized what I had when you were mine
I had go back to December, turn around and change my own mind
I go back to December all the time

[Bridge]
I miss your tan skin, your sweet smile
So good to me, so right
And how you held me in your arms that September night
The first time you ever saw me cry
Maybe this is wishful thinking
Probably mindless dreaming
But if we loved again, I swear I had love you right
I had go back in time and change it, but I cannot
So if the chain is on your door, I understand
[Chorus]
But this is me swallowing my pride
Standing in front of you, saying I am sorry for that night
And I go back to December
It turns out freedom am not nothing but missing you
Wishing I had realized what I had when you were mine
I had go back to December, turn around and make it alright
I had go back to December, turn around and change my own mind
I go back to December all the time
All the time

title: Thug Story
lyrics:
[Intro: T-Pain]
Hey Hey, T-Swizzle (T-Swizzle)
T-Pizzle (T-Pizzle)

[Verse 1: Taylor Swift]
I am like eight foot fo', blonde hair to the floor
You shorties never thought I dreamed about rapping hardcore
No I am not got a gun, no I never really been in a club
Still live with my parents, but I am still a thug
I am so gangster, you can find me baking cookies at night
You out clubbing but I just made caramel delights
T-Swift and T-Pain rapping on the same track
It's a thug story, tell me can you handle that?

[Verse 2: Taylor Swift & T-Pain & Both]
I had a dream last night
I had high top Nikes
I had diamonds in my mouth
And diamonds on my mic
By the time I woke I was singing
I am on a boat, whoa oh-oh
'Cause I am a singer turned rapper
Shorty I am a make ya
Straight to the top, yo
Shorty I am a take ya
You can call me T-Sweezy

Hey, It's a thug story
Now tell 'em who you are
Singer turned gangster
You do not want to fight me
Straight to the top
In my extra small white tee
[Bridge: T-Pain]
T-Swift and T-Pain all up on the same track

What? What? Don't test me (beep)!
Hey, hold on...
Hold on, I did not even say anything
I did not even s-
What?
I said Yo
Yup
You guys bleeped me and I did not even say anything
I did not even swear

Hello? Ugh!

title: Speak Now
lyrics:
[Verse 1]
I am not the kind of girl
Who should be rudely barging in
On a white veil occasion
But you are not the kind of boy
Who should be marrying the wrong girl
I sneak in and see your friends
And her snotty little family
All dressed in pastel
And she is yelling at a bridesmaid
Somewhere back inside a room
Wearing a gown shaped like a pastry

[Pre-Chorus]
This is surely not
What you thought it would be
I lose myself in a daydream
Where I stand and say

[Chorus]
Don't say yes, run away now
I shall meet you when you are out
Of the church, at the back door
Don't wait or say a single vow
You need to hear me out
And they said, "Speak now"
[Verse 2]
Fond gestures are exchanged
And the organ starts to play
A song that sounds like a death march
And I am hiding in the curtains
It seems that I was uninvited
By your lovely bride-to-be

[Pre-Chorus]
She floats down the aisle
Like a pageant queen
But I know you wish it was me
You wish it was me (Don't you?)

[Chorus]
Don't say yes, run away now
I shall meet you when you are out
Of the church, at the back door
Don't wait or say a single vow
You need to hear me out
And they said, "Speak now"
Don't say yes, run away now
I shall meet you when you are out
Of the church, at the back door
Don't wait or say a single vow
Your time is running out
And they said, "Speak now"
[Interlude]
Ooh, la-da-da-da, oh
Ooh, ooh
(Say a single vow)

[Bridge]
I hear the preacher say
"Speak now or forever hold your peace"
There's the silence, there has my last chance
I stand up with shaking hands, all eyes on me
Horrified looks from everyone in the room
But I am only looking at you

[Verse 3]
I am not the kind of girl
Who should be rudely barging in
On a white veil occasion
But you are not the kind of boy
Who should be marrying the wrong girl
(Hehe!)

[Chorus 2]
So do not say yes, run away now
I shall meet you when you are out
Of the church, at the back door
Don't wait or say a single vow
You need to hear me out
And they said, "Speak now"
And you say, "Let's run away now
I shall meet you when I am out
Of my tux, at the back door
Baby, I did not say my vows
So glad you were around
When they said, 'Speak now'"

title: Haunted
lyrics:
[Verse 1]
You and I walk a fragile line
I have known it all this time
But I never thought I had live to see it break
It's getting dark and it has all so quiet
And I cannot trust anything now
And it has coming over you like it has all a big mistake

[Pre-Chorus]
Whoa, holding my breath
Won't lose you again
Something's made your eyes go cold

[Chorus]
Come on, come on, do not leave me like this
I thought I had you figured out
Something's gone terribly wrong
You're all I wanted
Come on, come on, do not leave me like this
I thought I had you figured out
Can't breathe whenever you are gone
Can't turn back now, I am haunted
[Verse 2]
Stood there and watched you walk away
From everything we had
But I still mean every word I said to you
He will try to take away my pain
And he just might make me smile
But the whole time, I am wishing he was you instead

[Pre-Chorus]
Oh, holding my breath
Won't see you again
Something keeps me holding onto nothing

[Chorus]
Come on, come on, do not leave me like this
I thought I had you figured out
Something's gone terribly wrong
You're all I wanted
Come on, come on, do not leave me like this
I thought I had you figured out
Can't breathe whenever you are gone
Can't turn back now, I am haunted

[Bridge]
I know, I know
I just know
You're not gone
You cannot be gone, no
[Chorus]
Come on, come on, do not leave me like this
I thought I had you figured out
Something's gone terribly wrong
Won't finish what you started
Come on, come on, do not leave me like this
I thought I had you figured out
Can't breathe whenever you are gone
I cannot go back, I am haunted

[Outro]
Oh-oh, oh-oh, oh-oh, oh
You and I walk a fragile line
I have known it all this time
Never ever thought I had see it break
Never thought I had see it

 Never thought I had see it

Drew looks at me
I fake a smile so he will not see

Everything that we should be

[Pre-Chorus]

He's finally got it right
I wonder if he knows he has all I think about at night
[Chorus]
He's the reason for the teardrops on my guitar
The only thing that keeps me wishing on a wishing star
He's the song in the car I keep singing
Don't know why I do

The kind of flawless I wish I could be

The only one who’s got enough for me to break my heart
He's the song in the car I keep singing
Don't know why I do
He's the time taken up, but there has never enough
And he has all that I need to fall into

I fake a smile so he will not see

title: Youre Not Sorry
lyrics:
[Verse 1]
All this time I was wasting hoping you would come around
I have been giving out chances every time and all you do is let me down
And it has taken me this long, baby, but I have figured you out
And you are thinking we will be fine again, but not this time around

[Chorus]
You do not have to call anymore
I will not pick up the phone
This is the last straw
Don't wanna hurt anymore
And you can tell me that you are sorry
But I do not believe you, baby, like I did before
You're not sorry (No no no no)

[Verse 2]
You're looking so innocent, I might believe you if I did not know
Could've loved you all my life if you had not left me waiting in the cold
And you hav got your share of secrets
And I am tired of being last to know, oh
And now you are asking me to listen because it has worked each time before
[Chorus]
But you do not have to call anymore
I will not pick up the phone
This is the last straw
Don't wanna hurt anymore
And you can tell me that you are sorry
But I do not believe you, baby, like I did before
You're not sorry (No no no no)
You're not sorry (No no no no)

[Bridge]
You had me crawling for you, honey, and it never would have gone away, no
You used to shine so bright, but I watched all of it fade

[Chorus]
So you do not have to call anymore
I will not pick up the phone
This is the last straw
There's nothing left to beg for

But I do not believe you, baby, like I did before
You're not sorry (No no no no)
You're not sorry (No no no no)
(No, no, no, no, no, no, no, no, no, no, no, no)
Woah, oh, oh oh, oh oh oh
(Oh, oh, oh, no, no, no, no, no, no)

title: Better Than Revenge
lyrics:
[Intro]
Now go stand in the corner and think about what you did
Ha, time for a little revenge

[Verse 1]
The story starts when it was hot and it was summer and
I had it all, I had him right there where I wanted him
She came along, got him alone and let us hear the applause
She took him faster than you can say "Sabotage"
I never saw it coming, would not have suspected it
I underestimated just who I was dealing with
She had to know the pain was beating on me like a drum
She underestimated just who she was stealing from

[Chorus]
She has not a saint and she has not what you think
She has an actress, whoa
She has better known for the things that she does
On the mattress, whoa
Soon she has gonna find stealing other people's toys
On the playground will not make you many friends
She should keep in mind, she should keep in mind
There is nothing I do better than revenge, ha
[Verse 2]
She looks at life like it has a party and she has on the list
She looks at me like I am a trend and she has so over it
I think her ever-present frown is a little troubling
And she thinks I am psycho because I like to rhyme her name with things
But sophistication is not what you wear or who you know
Or pushing people down to get you where you wanna go
Oh, they did not teach you that in prep school so it has up to me
But no amount of vintage dresses gives you dignity
(Think about what you did)

[Chorus]
She has not a saint and she has not what you think
She has an actress, whoa
She has better known for the things that she does
On the mattress, whoa
Soon she has gonna find stealing other people's toys
On the playground will not make you many friends
She should keep in mind, she should keep in mind
There is nothing I do better than revenge, ha

[Bridge]
I am just another thing for you to roll your eyes at, honey
You might have him, but have not you heard?
I am just another thing for you to roll your eyes at, honey
You might have him, but I always get the last word
Whoa, whoa-ah-oh
[Chorus]
She has not a saint and she has not what you think
She has an actress, whoa (She deserved it)
She has better known for the things that she does
On the mattress, whoa
Soon she has gonna find stealing other people's toys
On the playground will not make you many friends
She should keep in mind, she should keep in mind
There is nothing I do better than revenge, ha

[Outro]
Do you still feel like you know what you are doing?
'Cause I do not think you do, oh (No, no, no, no)
Do you still feel like you know what you are doing? (No)
I do not think you do, I do not think you do
Let's hear the applause (Come on, come on)
Come on, show me how much better you are
(So much better, yeah?)
See you deserve some applause
'Cause you are so much better
She took him faster than you could say "Sabotage"

title: Enchanted
lyrics:
[Verse 1]
There I was again tonight
Forcing laughter, faking smiles
Same old tired, lonely place
Walls of insincerity, shifting eyes and vacancy
Vanished when I saw your face
All I can say is, it was enchanting to meet you

[Verse 2]
Your eyes whispered, "Have we met?"
'Cross the room your silhouette
Starts to make its way to me
The playful conversation starts
Counter all your quick remarks
Like passing notes in secrecy

[Pre-Chorus]
And it was enchanting to meet you
All I can say is, I was enchanted to meet you

[Chorus]
This night is sparkling
Don't you let it go
I am wonderstruck
Blushing all the way home
I shall spend forever
Wondering if you knew
I was enchanted to meet you
[Verse 3]
The lingering question kept me up
2 AM, who do you love?
I wonder 'til I am wide awake
And now I am pacing back and forth
Wishing you were at my door
I had open up and you would say, "Hey"

[Pre-Chorus]
It was enchanting to meet you
All I know is I was enchanted to meet you

[Chorus]
This night is sparkling
Don't you let it go
I am wonderstruck
Blushing all the way home
I shall spend forever
Wondering if you knew
This night is flawless
Don't you let it go
I am wonderstruck
Dancing around all alone
I shall spend forever
Wondering if you knew
I was enchanted to meet you
[Guitar Solo]

[Bridge]
This is me praying that
This was the very first page
Not where the storyline ends
My thoughts will echo your name
Until I see you again
These are the words I held back
As I was leaving too soon
I was enchanted to meet you

[Breakdown]
Please do not be in love
With someone else
Please do not have somebody
Waiting on you
Please do not be in love (Ooh)
With someone else
Please do not have somebody (Ooh, hey)
Waiting on you

[Chorus]
This night is sparkling
Don't you let it go
I am wonderstruck
Blushing all the way home
I shall spend forever
Wondering if you knew
This night is flawless (Please do not be in love with someone else)
Don't you let it go
I am wonderstruck (Please do not have somebody waiting on you)
Dancing around all alone
I shall spend forever (Please do not be in love with someone else)
Wondering if you knew
I was enchanted to meet you
[Outro]
Please do not be in love
With someone else
Please do not have somebody
Waiting on you

title: Safe  Sound
lyrics:
[Verse 1: Taylor Swift]
I remember tears streaming down your face
When I said I shall never let you go
When all those shadows almost killed your light
I remember you said, "Don't leave me here alone"

[Chorus: Taylor Swift with Joy Williams of the Civil Wars backup]

The sun is going down
You'll be alright
No one can hurt you now

Gone

The sun is going down

[Chorus]
Just close your eyes
You'll be alright
Come morning light
You and I shall be safe and sound

title: Dear John
lyrics:
[Verse 1]
Long were the nights when
My days once revolved around you
Counting my footsteps
Praying the floor will not fall through... again
My mother accused me of losing my mind
But I swore I was fine
You paint me a blue sky
Then go back and turn it to rain
And I lived in your chess game
But you changed the rules everyday
Wonderin' which version of you I might get on the phone, tonight
Well, I stopped pickin' up and this song is to let you know why

[Chorus]
Dear John, I see it all now that you are gone
Don't you think I was too young to be messed with?
The girl in the dress cried the whole way home
I should have known

[Verse 2]
Well, maybe it has me
And my blind optimism to blame
Or maybe it has you and your sick need
To give love and take it away
And you shall add my name to your long list of traitors
Who do not understand
And I look back in regret how I ignored when they said
"Run as fast as you can"
[Chorus]
Dear John, I see it all now that you are gone
Don't you think I was too young to be messed with?
The girl in the dress cried the whole way home
Dear John, I see it all now, it was wrong
Don't you think nineteen's too young
To be played by your dark, twisted games
When I loved you so?
I should have known

[Bridge]
You are an expert at sorry

title: Innocent
lyrics:
[Verse 1]
I guess you really did it this time
Left yourself in your war path
Lost your balance on a tightrope
Lost your mind trying to get it back

[Pre-Chorus]
Wasn't it easier in your lunchbox days?
Always a bigger bed to crawl into
Wasn't it beautiful when you believed in everything
And everybody believed in you?

[Chorus]
It's alright, just wait and see
Your string of lights is still bright to me
Oh, who you are is not where you hav been
You're still an innocent, you are still an innocent

[Verse 2]
Did some things you cannot speak of
But at night you live it all again
You would not be shattered on the floor now
If only you had seen what you know now then
[Pre-Chorus]
Wasn't it easier in your firefly-catching days?
When everything out of reach
Someone bigger brought down to you
Wasn't it beautiful running wild 'til you fell asleep
Before the monsters caught up to you?

[Chorus]
It's alright, just wait and see
Your string of lights is still bright to me
Oh, who you are is not where you hav been
You're still an innocent
It's okay, life is a tough crowd
32 and still growing up now
Who you are is not what you did
You're still an innocent

[Bridge]
Time turns flames to embers
You'll have new Septembers
Every one of us has messed up too, ooh
Minds change like the weather
I hope you remember
Today is never too late to be brand new, oh

[Chorus]
It's alright, just wait and see
Your string of lights is still bright to me
Oh, who you are is not where you hav been
You're still an innocent
It's okay, life is a tough crowd
32 and still growing up now
Who you are is not what you did
You're still an innocent, you are still an innocent
[Outro]
Lost your balance on a tightrope, oh
It's never too late to get it back

title: We Are Never Ever Getting Back Together
lyrics:
[Verse 1]
I remember when we broke up the first time
Saying, "This is it, I have had enough," because like
We had not seen each other in a month
When you said you needed space (What?)
Then you come around again and say
"Baby, I miss you and I swear I am gonna change, trust me"
Remember how that lasted for a day?
I say, "I hate you," we break up, you call me, "I love you"

[Pre-Chorus]
Ooh-ooh-ooh-ooh-ooh
We called it off again last night, but
Ooh-ooh-ooh-ooh-ooh
This time, I am telling you, I am telling you

[Chorus]
We are never, ever, ever getting back together
We are never, ever, ever getting back together
You go talk to your friends, talk to my friends, talk to me
But we are never, ever, ever, ever
Getting back together
Like, ever
[Verse 2]
I am really gonna miss you picking fights
And me falling for it, screaming that I am right
And you would hide away and find your peace of mind
With some indie record that has much cooler than mine

[Pre-Chorus]
Ooh-ooh-ooh-ooh-ooh
You called me up again tonight, but
Ooh-ooh-ooh-ooh-ooh
This time, I am telling you, I am telling you

[Chorus]
We (We) are never, ever, ever getting back together
We are never, ever, ever getting back together
You go talk to your friends, talk to my friends, talk to me
(Talk to me) But we are never, ever, ever, ever
Getting back together

[Post-Chorus]
Ooh-ooh-ooh-ooh-ooh (Yeah)
Ooh-ooh-ooh-ooh-ooh-ooh (Yeah)
Ooh-ooh-ooh-ooh-ooh (Yeah)
Oh-oh-oh

[Bridge]
I used to think that we were forever, ever
And I used to say, "Never say never"
Ugh, so he calls me up and he has like, "I still love you"
And I am like, "I just, I mean, this is exhausting, you know?
Like, we are never getting back together, like, ever"
[Chorus]
(No) We are never, ever, ever getting back together
We are never, ever, ever (Ooh) getting back together

Getting back together

Getting back together (Yeah)

title: The Best Day
lyrics:
[Verse 1]
I am five years old, it has getting cold, I have got my big coat on
I hear your laugh and look up smiling at you, I run and run
Past the pumpkin patch and the tractor rides
Look now, the sky is gold
I hug your legs and fall asleep on the way home

[Chorus 1]
I do not know why all the trees change in the fall
But I know you are not scared of anything at all
Don't know if Snow White's house is near or far away
But I know I had the best day with you today

[Verse 2]
I am thirteen now
And do not know how my friends could be so mean
I come home crying and you hold me tight and grab the keys
And we drive and drive until we found a town far enough away
And we talk and window shop 'til I have forgotten all their names

[Chorus 2]
I do not know who I am going to talk to now at school
But I know I am laughing on the car ride home with you
Don't know how long it has going to take to feel okay
But I know I had the best day with you today
[Bridge]
I have an excellent father, his strength is making me stronger
God smiles on my little brother, inside and out
He's better than I am
I grew up in a pretty house and I had space to run
And I had the best days with you

[Verse 3]
There is a video I found from back when I was three
You set up a paint set in the kitchen and you are talking to me
It's the age of princesses and pirate ships and the seven dwarfs
And Daddy's smart
And you are the prettiest lady in the whole wide world

[Chorus 3]
And now I know why all the trees change in the fall
I know you were on my side even when I was wrong
And I love you for giving me your eyes
For staying back and watching me shine
And I did not know if you knew, so I am taking this chance to say
That I had the best day with you today

title: I Knew You Were Trouble.

[Verse 1]
Once upon a time, a few mistakes ago
I was in your sights, you got me alone
You found me, you found me
You found me-e-e-e-e
I guess you did not care, and I guess I liked that
And when I fell hard, you took a step back
Without me, without me
Without me-e-e-e-e

title: Red
lyrics:
[Verse 1]
Loving him is like driving a new Maserati down a dead-end street
Faster than the wind, passionate as sin, ending so suddenly
Loving him is like trying to change your mind once you are already flying through the free fall
Like the colors in autumn, so bright just before they lose it all

[Chorus]
Losing him was blue like I had never known
Missing him was dark gray, all alone
Forgetting him was like trying to know somebody you hav never met
But loving him was red

[Post-Chorus]
(Red, red)
(Red, red)
Loving him was red
(Red, red)
(Red, red)

[Verse 2]
Touching him was like realizing all you ever wanted was right there in front of you
Memorizing him was as easy as knowing all the words to your old favorite song
Fighting with him was like trying to solve a crossword and realizing there has no right answer
Regretting him was like wishing you never found out that love could be that strong
[Chorus]
Losing him was blue like I had never known
Missing him was dark gray, all alone (Whoa)
Forgetting him was like trying to know somebody you hav never met
But loving him was red

[Post-Chorus]
(Red, red)
Oh, red (Red, red)
Burning red (Red, red)
(Red, red)

[Bridge]
Remembering him comes in flashbacks and echoes
Tell myself it has time now, gotta let go
But moving on from him is impossible
When I still see it all in my head
In burning red
Burning, it was red

[Chorus]
Oh, losing him was blue like I had never known
Missing him was dark gray, all alone (Whoa)
Forgetting him was like trying to know somebody you hav never met
'Cause loving him was red
[Post-Chorus]
(Red, red) Yeah, yeah, red (Red, red)
Burning red (Red, red)
(Red, red)

[Breakdown]
And that has why (Red, red) he has spinning 'round in my head
Comes back to me (Red, red), burning red
(Red, red) Yeah, yeah
(Red, red)

[Outro]
His love was like driving a new Maserati down a dead-end street

title: Begin Again
lyrics:
[Verse 1]
Took a deep breath in the mirror
He did not like it when I wore high heels
But I do
Turn the lock and put my headphones on
He always said he did not get this song
But I do, I do

[Verse 2]
Walked in, expecting you had be late
But you got here early and you stand and wave
I walk to you
You pull my chair out and help me in
And you do not know how nice that is
But I do

[Chorus]
And you throw your head back laughing like a little kid
I think it has strange that you think I am funny because he never did
I have been spending the last eight months
Thinking all love ever does is break, and burn, and end
But on a Wednesday in a café, I watched it begin again
[Verse 3]
You said you never met one girl who
Had as many James Taylor records as you
But I do
We tell stories and you do not know why
I am coming off a little shy
But I do

[Chorus]
But you throw your head back laughing like a little kid
I think it has strange that you think I am funny because he never did
I have been spending the last eight months
Thinking all love ever does is break, and burn, and end
But on a Wednesday in a café, I watched it begin again

[Instrumental Break]

[Bridge]
And we walked down the block to my car
And I almost brought him up
But you start to talk about the movies
That your family watches every single Christmas
And I want to talk about that
And for the first time, what has past is past

[Chorus]
'Cause you throw your head back laughing like a little kid
I think it has strange that you think I am funny because he never did
I have been spending the last eight months
Thinking all love ever does is break, and burn, and end
But on a Wednesday in a café, I watched it begin again
[Outro]
But on a Wednesday in a café, I watched it begin again

title: Everything Has Changed
lyrics:
[Intro: Ed Sheeran]
(You good to go?)

[Verse 1: Taylor Swift]
All I knew this morning when I woke
Is I know something now
Know something now I did not before
And all I have seen since 18 hours ago
Is green eyes and freckles and your smile
In the back of my mind, making me feel like

[Pre-Chorus: Taylor Swift &  Ed Sheeran]
I just wanna know you better
Know you better, know you better now
I just wanna know you better
Know you better, know you better now
I just wanna know you better
Know you better, know you better now
I just wanna know you, know you, know you

[Chorus: Taylor Swift & Ed Sheeran]

And your eyes look like coming home
All I know is a simple name
Everything has changed
All I know is you held the door
You'll be mine and I shall be yours
All I know since yesterday
Is everything has changed
[Verse 2: Ed Sheeran & Taylor Swift]
And all my walls stood tall, painted blue
And I shall take 'em down, take 'em down
And open up the door for you
And all I feel in my stomach is butterflies

title: You Belong with Me
lyrics:
[Verse 1]
You're on the phone with your girlfriend, she has upset
She has going off about something that you said
'Cause she does not get your humor like I do
I am in the room, it has a typical Tuesday night
I am listening to the kind of music she does not like
And she shall never know your story like I do

[Pre-Chorus]
But she wears short skirts, I wear T-shirts
She has Cheer Captain and I am on the bleachers
Dreaming about the day when you wake up and find
That what you are looking for has been here the whole time

[Chorus]
If you could see that I am the one who understands you
Been here all along, so why cannot you see?
You belong with me, you belong with me

[Verse 2]
Walking the streets with you and your worn-out jeans
I cannot help thinking this is how it ought to be
Laughing on a park bench, thinking to myself
Hey, is not this easy?
And you hav got a smile that could light up this whole town
I have not seen it in a while since she brought you down
You say you are fine, I know you better than that
Hey, whatcha doing with a girl like that?
[Pre-Chorus]
She wears high heels, I wear sneakers
She has Cheer Captain and I am on the bleachers
Dreaming about the day when you wake up and find
That what you are looking for has been here the whole time

[Chorus]
If you could see that I am the one who understands you
Been here all along, so why cannot you see?
You belong with me
Standing by and waiting at your back door
All this time how could you not know, baby?
You belong with me, you belong with me

[Bridge]
Oh, I remember you driving to my house
In the middle of the night
I am the one who makes you laugh
When you know you are 'bout to cry
And I know your favorite songs
And you tell me 'bout your dreams
Think I know where you belong
Think I know it has with me

[Chorus]
Can't you see that I am the one who understands you
Been here all along, so why cannot you see?
You belong with me
Standing by and waiting at your back door
All this time how could you not know, baby?
You belong with me, you belong with me
[Outro]
You belong with me
Have you ever thought just maybe
You belong with me?
You belong with me

title: Breathe
lyrics:
[Verse 1: Taylor Swift]
I see your face in my mind as I drive away
'Cause none of us thought it was gonna end that way
People are people and sometimes we change our minds
But it has killing me to see you go after all this time

[Verse 2: Taylor Swift with Colbie Caillat]
Music starts playing like the end of a sad movie
It's the kind of ending you do not really wanna see
'Cause it has tragedy and it shall only bring you down
Now I do not know what to be without you around

[Pre-Chorus: Taylor Swift with Colbie Caillat]
And we know it has never simple, never easy
Never a clean break, no one here to save me
You're the only thing I know like the back of my hand

[Chorus: Taylor Swift with Colbie Caillat]
And I cannot breathe without you, but I have to
Breathe without you, but I have to
[Verse 3: Taylor Swift with Colbie Caillat]
Never wanted this, never wanna see you hurt
Every little bump in the road, I tried to swerve
But people are people and sometimes it does not work out
Nothing we say is gonna save us from the fall out

[Pre-Chorus: Taylor Swift with Colbie Caillat]
And we know it has never simple, never easy
Never a clean break, no one here to save me
You're the only thing I know like the back of my hand

[Chorus: Taylor Swift with Colbie Caillat]
And I cannot breathe without you, but I have to
Breathe without you but I have to

[Bridge: Taylor Swift with Colbie Caillat]
It's 2 A.M, feeling like I just lost a friend
Hope you know it has not easy, easy for me
It's 2 A.M, feeling like I just lost a friend
Hope you know this am not easy, easy for me

[Pre-Chorus: Taylor Swift with Colbie Caillat]
And we know it has never simple, never easy
Never a clean break, no one here to save me, oh-oh

[Chorus: Taylor Swift with Colbie Caillat]
I cannot breathe without you, but I have to
Breathe without you, but I have to
Breathe without you, but I have to
[Outro: Taylor Swift & Colbie Caillat]
I am sorry, I am sorry (Mmm)
I am sorry, (Yeah, yeah) I am sorry
I am sorry, I am sorry
I am sorry

title: Love Story
lyrics:
[Verse 1]
We were both young when I first saw you
I close my eyes, and the flashback starts
I am standing there
On a balcony in summer air
See the lights, see the party, the ball gowns
See you make your way through the crowd
And say, "Hello"
Little did I know

[Pre-Chorus]
That you were Romeo, you were throwing pebbles
And my daddy said, "Stay away from Juliet"
And I was crying on the staircase
Begging you, "Please do not go," and I said

[Chorus]
Romeo, take me somewhere we can be alone
I shall be waiting, all there has left to do is run
You'll be the prince and I shall be the princess
It's a love story, baby, just say "Yes"
[Verse 2]
So I sneak out to the garden to see you
We keep quiet, because we are dead if they knew
So close your eyes
Escape this town for a little while, oh, oh

[Pre-Chorus]
'Cause you were Romeo, I was a scarlet letter
And my daddy said, "Stay away from Juliet"
But you were everything to me
I was begging you, "Please do not go," and I said

[Chorus]
Romeo, take me somewhere we can be alone
I shall be waiting, all there has left to do is run
You'll be the prince and I shall be the princess
It's a love story, baby, just say "Yes"
Romeo, save me, they are trying to tell me how to feel
This love is difficult, but it has real
Don't be afraid, we will make it out of this mess
It's a love story, baby, just say "Yes"

[Post-Chorus]
Oh, oh

[Bridge]
I got tired of waiting
Wondering if you were ever coming around
My faith in you was fading
When I met you on the outskirts of town
[Breakdown]
And I said, "Romeo, save me, I have been feeling so alone
I keep waiting for you but you never come
Is this in my head? I do not know what to think"
He knelt to the ground and pulled out a ring, and said

[Chorus]
"Marry me, Juliet, you shall never have to be alone
I love you, and that has all I really know
I talked to your dad, go pick out a white dress
It's a love story, baby, just say 'Yes'"

[Outro]
Oh, oh, oh
Oh, oh, oh
'Cause we were both young when I first saw you

title: Fifteen
lyrics:
[Verse 1]
You take a deep breath and you walk through the doors
It's the mornin' of your very first day
You say hi to your friends you am not seen in a while
Try and stay out of everybody's way
It's your freshman year and you are gonna be here
For the next four years in this town
Hopin' one of those senior boys will wink at you and say
"You know, I have not seen you around before"

[Chorus]
'Cause when you are fifteen and somebody tells you they love you
You're gonna believe them
And when you are fifteen, feelin' like there has nothin' to figure out
Well, count to ten, take it in
This is life before you know who you are gonna be
Fifteen

[Verse 2]
You sit in class next to a redhead named Abigail
And soon enough, you are best friends
Laughin' at the other girls who think they are so cool
We'll be outta here as soon as we can
And then you are on your very first date and he has got a car
And you are feelin' like flyin'
And your mama's waitin' up and you are thinkin' he has the one
And you are dancin' 'round your room when the night ends
When the night ends
[Chorus]
'Cause when you are fifteen and somebody tells you they love you
You're gonna believe them
And when you are fifteen and your first kiss
Makes your head spin 'round
But in your life you shall do things greater than
Dating the boy on the football team
But I did not know it at fifteen

[Bridge]
When all you wanted was to be wanted
Wish you could go back and tell yourself what you know now
Back then, I swore I was gonna marry him someday
But I realized some bigger dreams of mine
And Abigail gave everything she had
To a boy who changed his mind
And we both cried

[Chorus]
'Cause when you are fifteen and somebody tells you they love you
You're gonna believe them
And when you are fifteen, do not forget to look before you fall
I have found time can heal most anything
And you just might find who you are supposed to be
I did not know who I was supposed to be
At fifteen
[Post-Chorus]
La-la-la, la-la-la, la-la-la-la
La-la-la, la-la-la, la-la-la-la
La-la-la, la-la-la

[Outro]
Your very first day
Take a deep breath, girl
Take a deep breath as you walk through the doors

title: Fearless
lyrics:
[Verse 1]
There's something 'bout the way
The street looks when it has just rained
There's a glow off the pavement, you walk me to the car
And you know I wanna ask you to dance right there
In the middle of the parking lot, yeah
Oh, yeah

[Verse 2]
We're driving down the road, I wonder if you know
I am trying so hard not to get caught up now
But you are just so cool, run your hands through your hair
Absentmindedly making me want you

[Chorus]
And I do not know how it gets better than this
You take my hand and drag me head first, fearless
And I do not know why but with you I had dance
In a storm in my best dress, fearless

[Verse 3]
So, baby, drive slow 'til we run out of road
In this one horse town, I wanna stay right here
In this passenger's seat
You put your eyes on me
In this moment now, capture it, remember it
[Chorus]
'Cause I do not know how it gets better than this
You take my hand and drag me head first, fearless
And I do not know why but with you I had dance
In a storm in my best dress, fearless

[Bridge]
Well, you stood there with me in the doorway
My hands shake, I am not usually this way but
You pull me in and I am a little more brave
It's the first kiss, it has flawless, really something
It's fearless
Oh, yeah

[Chorus]
'Cause I do not know how it gets better than this
You take my hand and drag me head first, fearless
And I do not know why but with you I had dance
In a storm in my best dress, fearless
'Cause I do not know how it gets better than this
You take my hand and drag me head first, fearless
And I do not know why but with you I had dance
In a storm in my best dress, fearless

[Outro]
Oh, oh
Oh, yeah

title: White Horse
lyrics:
[Verse 1]
Say you are sorry, that face of an angel
Comes out just when you need it to
As I paced back and forth all this time
'Cause I honestly believed in you
Holdin' on, the days drag on
Stupid girl, I shoulda known, I shoulda known

[Chorus]
That I am not a princess, this am not a fairytale
I am not the one you shall sweep off her feet, lead her up the stairwell
This am not Hollywood, this is a small town
I was a dreamer before you went and let me down
Now it has too late for you and your white horse
To come around

[Verse 2]
Maybe I was naive, got lost in your eyes
And never really had a chance
My mistake, I did not know to be in love
You had to fight to have the upper hand
I had so many dreams about you and me
Happy endings, now I know
[Chorus]
That I am not a princess, this am not a fairytale
I am not the one you shall sweep off her feet, lead her up the stairwell
This am not Hollywood, this is a small town
I was a dreamer before you went and let me down
Now it has too late for you and your white horse
To come around

[Bridge]
And there you are on your knees
Beggin' for forgiveness, beggin' for me
Just like I always wanted
But I am so sorry

[Chorus]
'Cause I am not your princess, this am not our fairytale
I am gonna find someone someday, who might actually treat me well
This is a big world, that was a small town
There in my rear view mirror disappearing now
And it has too late for you and your white horse
Now it has too late for you and your white horse
To catch me now

[Outro]
Oh, whoa, whoa, whoa
Try and catch me now, oh
It's too late to catch me now

title: Change
lyrics:
[Verse 1]
And it has a sad picture, the final blow hits you
Somebody else gets what you wanted again and
You know it has all the same, another time and place
Repeating history and you are getting sick of it
But I believe in whatever you do
And I shall do anything to see it through

[Chorus]
Because these things will change
Can you feel it now?
These walls that they put up to hold us back will fall down
This revolution, the time will come
For us to finally win
And we will sing hallelujah, we will sing hallelujah
Oh, oh

[Verse 2]
So we have been outnumbered, raided, and now cornered
It's hard to fight when the fight ain’t fair
We're getting stronger now, find things they never found
They might be bigger but we are faster and never scared
You can walk away, say we do not need this
But there has something in your eyes says we can beat this
[Chorus]
'Cause these things will change
Can you feel it now?
These walls that they put up to hold us back will fall down
This revolution, the time will come
For us to finally win
And we will sing hallelujah, we will sing hallelujah
Oh, oh

[Bridge]
Tonight we stand, get off our knees
Fight for what we have worked for all these years
And the battle was long, it has the fight of our lives
But we will stand up champions tonight

[Chorus]
It was the night things changed
Can you see it now?
These walls that they put up to hold us back fell down
It's a revolution, throw your hands up
'Cause we never gave in
And we will sing hallelujah, we sang hallelujah
Hallelujah

title: State of Grace
lyrics:
[Verse 1]
I am walking fast through the traffic lights
Busy streets and busy lives
And all we know is touch and go
We are alone with our changing minds
We fall in love 'til it hurts or bleeds
Or fades in time

[Chorus]
And I never (Never)
Saw you coming
And I’ll never (Never)
Be the same

[Verse 2]
You come around and the armor falls
Pierce the room like a cannonball
Now all we know is don’t let go
We are alone, just you and me
Up in your room and our slates are clean
Just twin fire signs, four blue eyes
[Pre-Chorus]
So you were never a saint
And I have loved in shades of wrong
We learn to live with the pain
Mosaic broken hearts
But this love is brave and wild

[Chorus]
And I never (Never)
Saw you coming
And I’ll never (Never)
Be the same

[Bridge]
This is a state of grace
This is the worthwhile fight
Love is a ruthless game
Unless you play it good and right
These are the hands of fate
You’re my Achilles heel
This is the golden age
Of something good and right and real

[Chorus]
And I never (Never)
Saw you coming
And I’ll never
Be the same
[Chorus]
And I never (Never)
Saw you coming
And I’ll never (So you were never a saint)
(And I have loved in shades of wrong)
Be the same (We learn to live with the pain)
(Mosaic broken hearts)
(But this love is brave and wild)

[Outro]
This is a state of grace
This is the worthwhile fight
Love is a ruthless game
Unless you play it good and right

title: Treacherous
lyrics:
[Verse 1]
Put your lips close to mine
As long as they do not touch
Out of focus, eye to eye
'Til the gravity's too much
And I shall do anything you say
If you say it with your hands
And I had be smart to walk away
But you are quicksand

[Chorus]
This slope is treacherous
This path is reckless
This slope is treacherous
And I-I-I like it

[Verse 2]
I cannot decide if it has a choice
Getting swept away
I hear the sound of my own voice
Asking you to stay
And all we are is skin and bone
Trained to get along
Forever going with the flow
But you are friction
[Chorus]
This slope is treacherous
This path is reckless
This slope is treacherous
I, I, I like it

[Bridge]
Two headlights shine through the sleepless night
And I will get you, get you alone
Your name has echoed through my mind
And I just think you should, think you should know
That nothing safe is worth the drive
And I would follow you, follow you home
I shall follow you, follow you home

[Chorus]
This hope is treacherous
This daydream is dangerous
This hope is treacherous
I-I-I, I-I-I, I-I-I

[Bridge]
Two headlights shine through the sleepless night
And I will get you, get you alone
Your name has echoed through my mind
And I just think you should, think you should know
That nothing safe is worth the drive
And I would follow you, follow you home
I shall follow you, follow you home
I shall follow you, follow you home
I shall follow you, follow you home
[Outro]
This slope is treacherous
I-I-I like it

title: All Too Well
lyrics:
[Verse 1]
I walked through the door with you, the air was cold
But something 'bout it felt like home somehow
And I left my scarf there at your sister's house
And you hav still got it in your drawer, even now

[Verse 2]
Oh, your sweet disposition and my wide-eyed gaze
We're singing in the car, getting lost upstate
Autumn leaves falling down like pieces into place
And I can picture it after all these days

[Pre-Chorus]
And I know it has long gone and
That magic's not here no more
And I might be okay, but I am not fine at all
Oh, oh, oh

[Chorus]
'Cause there we are again on that little town street
You almost ran the red because you were lookin' over at me
Wind in my hair, I was there
I remember it all too well
[Verse 3]
Photo album on the counter, your cheeks were turning red
You used to be a little kid with glasses in a twin-sized bed
And your mother's telling stories 'bout you on the tee-ball team
You taught me 'bout your past, thinking your future was me

[Pre-Chorus]
And I know it has long gone and
There was nothing else I could do
And I forget about you long enough
To forget why I needed to

[Chorus]
'Cause there we are again in the middle of the night
We're dancing ‘round the kitchen in the refrigerator light
Down the stairs, I was there
I remember it all too well, yeah

[Bridge]
Well maybe we got lost in translation
Maybe I asked for too much
But maybe this thing was a masterpiece
'Til you tore it all up
Running scared, I was there
I remember it all too well
And you call me up again
Just to break me like a promise
So casually cruel in the name of being honest
I am a crumpled up piece of paper lying here
'Cause I remember it all, all, all
Too well
[Verse 4]
Time will not fly, it has like I am paralyzed by it
I had like to be my old self again, but I am still trying to find it
After plaid shirt days and nights when you made me your own
Now you mail back my things and I walk home alone
But you keep my old scarf from that very first week
'Cause it reminds you of innocence and it smells like me
You cannot get rid of it
'Cause you remember it all too well, yeah

[Chorus]
'Cause there we are again when I loved you so
Back before you lost the one real thing you hav ever known
It was rare, I was there
I remember it all too well

[Outro]
Wind in my hair, you were there
You remember it all
Down the stairs, you were there
You remember it all
It was rare, I was there
I remember it all too well

title: Stay Stay Stay
lyrics:
[Verse 1]
I am pretty sure we almost broke up last night
I threw my phone across the room, at you
I was expecting some dramatic turn away
But you stayed
This morning, I said we should talk about it
'Cause I read you should never leave a fight unresolved
That's when you came in wearing a football helmet
And said, "Okay, let us talk"
And I said

[Chorus]
Stay, stay, stay
I have been loving you for quite some time, time, time
You think that it has funny when I am mad, mad, mad
But I think that it has best if we both stay

[Verse 2]
Before you, I had only dated self-indulgent takers
Who took all of their problems out on me
But you carry my groceries and now I am always laughing
And I love you because you have given me
No choice but to
[Chorus]
Stay, stay, stay
I have been loving you for quite some time, time, time
You think that it has funny when I am mad, mad, mad
But I think that it has best if we both stay, stay, stay, stay

[Bridge]
You took the time to memorize me
My fears, my hopes, and dreams
I just like hanging out with you, all the time
All those times that you did not leave, it has been occurring to me
I had like to hang out with you, for my whole life

[Breakdown]
Stay, and I shall be loving you for quite some time
No one else is gonna love me when I get mad, mad, mad
So I think that it has best if we both stay, stay
Stay, stay, stay, stay!

[Chorus]
Stay, stay, stay
I have been loving you for quite some time, time, time
You think that it has funny when I am mad, mad, mad
But I think that it has best if we both stay, stay
Stay, stay, stay, stay!
[Outro]
Stay, stay, stay
I have been loving you for quite some time, time, time
You think that it has funny when I am mad, mad, mad
But I think that it has best if we both stay
(Ha-ha-ha, it has so fun)

lyrics:

Find myself at your door
Just like all those times before
I’m not sure how I got there
All roads they lead me here
I imagine you are home
In your room, all alone

And everything feels better

[Pre-Chorus: Both]
And right before your eyes
I am breaking, no past
No reasons why
Just you and me

title: Holy Ground
lyrics:
[Verse 1]
I was reminiscing just the other day
While having coffee all alone, and Lord, it took me away
Back to a first-glance feeling on New York time
Back when you fit in my poems like a perfect rhyme
Took off faster than a green light, go
Hey, you skip the conversation when you already know
I left a note on the door with a joke we had made
And that was the first day

[Chorus]
And darling, it was good
Never looking down
And right there where we stood
Was holy ground

[Verse 2]
Spinning like a girl in a brand new dress
We had this big wide city all to ourselves
We blocked the noise with the sound of, "I need you"
And for the first time, I had something to lose
And I guess we fell apart in the usual way
And the story's got dust on every page
But sometimes, I wonder how you think about it now
And I see your face in every crowd
[Chorus]
'Cause darling, it was good
Never looking down
And right there where we stood
Was holy ground

[Bridge]
Tonight, I am gonna dance
For all that we have been through
But I do not wanna dance
If I am not dancing with you
Tonight, I am gonna dance
Like you were in this room
But I do not wanna dance
If I am not dancing with you

[Chorus]
It was good
Never looking down
And right there where we stood
Was holy ground

[Outro]
Tonight, I am gonna dance
For all that we have been through
But I do not wanna dance
If I am not dancing with you
Tonight, I am gonna dance
Like you were in this room
But I do not wanna dance
If I am not dancing with you

title: Sad Beautiful Tragic
lyrics:
[Verse 1]
Long handwritten note, deep in your pocket
Words, how little they mean, when you are a little too late
I stood right by the tracks, your face in a locket
Good girls, hopeful they shall be and long they will wait

[Chorus]
We had a beautiful magic love there
What a sad, beautiful, tragic love affair

[Verse 2]
In dreams, I meet you in warm conversation
We both wake in lonely beds, different cities
And time is taking its sweet time erasing you
And you hav got your demons, and darling, they all look like me

[Chorus]
'Cause we had a beautiful magic love there
What a sad, beautiful, tragic love affair

[Bridge]
Distance, timing
Breakdown, fighting
Silence, the train runs off its tracks
Kiss me, try to fix it
Could you just try to listen?
Hang up, give up
And for the life of us we cannot get back
[Breakdown]
A beautiful, magic love there
What a sad, beautiful, tragic
Beautiful, tragic, beautiful

[Chorus]
What we had, a beautiful magic love there
What a sad, beautiful, tragic, love affair
We had a beautiful magic love there
What a sad, beautiful, tragic love affair

title: The Lucky One
lyrics:
[Verse 1]
New to town with a made-up name
In the angel's city, chasing fortune and fame
And the camera flashes make it look like a dream
You had it figured out since you were in school
Everybody loves pretty, everybody loves cool
So overnight, you look like a sixties queen

[Pre-Chorus 1]
Another name goes up in lights
Like diamonds in the sky

[Chorus 1]
And they’ll tell you now, you’re the lucky one
Yeah, they’ll tell you now, you’re the lucky one
But can you tell me now, you’re the lucky one?
Oh, oh, oh

[Verse 2]
Now, it’s big black cars and Riviera views
And your lover in the foyer doesn’t even know you
And your secrets end up splashed on the news front page
And they tell you that you’re lucky, but you’re so confused
'Cause you don’t feel pretty, you just feel used
And all the young things line up to take your place
[Pre-Chorus 2]
Another name goes up in lights
You wonder if you’ll make it out alive

[Chorus 1]
And they’ll tell you now, you’re the lucky one
Yeah, they’ll tell you now, you’re the lucky one
But can you tell me now, you’re the lucky one?
Oh, oh, oh

[Verse 3]
It was a few years later, I showed up here
And they still tell the legend of how you disappeared
How you took the money and your dignity and got the hell out
They say you bought a bunch of land somewhere
Chose the rose garden over Madison Square
And it took some time, but I understand it now

[Pre-Chorus 3]
‘Cause now my name is up in lights
But I think you got it right

[Chorus 2]
Let me tell you now, you’re the lucky one
Let me tell you now, you’re the lucky one
Let me tell you now, you’re the lucky one, oh, oh, oh
And they’ll tell you now, you’re the lucky one
Yeah, they’ll tell you now, you’re the lucky one
And they’ll tell you now, you’re the lucky one, oh, oh, oh
Oh, whoa, oh, oh

title: Starlight
lyrics:
[Chorus]
I said, "Oh, my, what a marvelous tune"
It was the best night, never would forget how we moved
The whole place was dressed to the nines
And we were dancing, dancing
Like we are made of starlight
Like we are made of starlight

[Verse 1]
I met Bobby on the boardwalk, summer of '45
Picked me up, late one night at the window
We were 17 and crazy, running wild, wild
Can't remember what song it was playing when we walked in
The night we snuck into a yacht club party
Pretending to be a duchess and a prince

[Chorus]
And I said, "Oh, my, what a marvelous tune"
It was the best night, never would forget how we moved
The whole place was dressed to the nines
And we were dancing, dancing
Like we are made of starlight, starlight
Like we are made of starlight, starlight
[Verse 2]

title: The Moment I Knew
lyrics:
[Verse 1]
You should have been there
Should've burst through the door
With that "Baby, I am right here" smile
And it would have felt like
A million little shining stars had just aligned
And I would have been so happy

[Verse 2]
Christmas lights glisten
I have got my eye on the door
Just waiting for you to walk in
But the time is ticking
People ask me how I have been
As I comb back through my memory
How you said you had be here
You said you had be here

[Chorus]
And it was like slow motion
Standing there in my party dress
In red lipstick
With no one to impress
And they are all laughing
As I am looking around the room
But there was one thing missing
And that was the moment I knew
[Verse 3]
And the hours pass by
Now I just wanna be alone
But your close friends always seem to know
When there has something really wrong
So they follow me down the hall
And there in the bathroom
I try not to fall apart
And the sinking feeling starts
As I say hopelessly
"He said he had be here"

[Chorus]
And it was like slow motion
Standing there in my party dress
In red lipstick
With no one to impress
And they are all laughing
And asking me about you
But there was one thing missing (Missing)
And that was the moment I knew

[Bridge]
What do you say
When tears are streaming down your face
In front of everyone you know?
And what do you do
When the one who means the most to you
Is the one who did not show?
[Breakdown]
You should have been here
And I would have been so happy

[Chorus]
And it was like slow motion
Standing there in my party dress
In red lipstick
With no one to impress
And they are all standing around me, singing
"Happy birthday to you"
But there was one thing missing
And that was the moment I knew
Oh-oh-oh-oh-oh-oh-oh, I knew
Oh-oh-oh-oh-oh-oh-oh

[Outro]
You called me later
And said, "I am sorry I did not make it"
And I said, "I am sorry, too"
And that was the moment I knew

title: Come Back... Be Here
lyrics:
[Verse 1]
You said it in a simple way
4 AM, the second day
How strange that I do not know you at all
Stumbled through the long goodbye
One last kiss, then catch your flight
Right when I was just about to fall

[Pre-Chorus 1]
I told myself, do not get attached
But in my mind, I play it back
Spinning faster than the plane that took you

[Chorus]
And this is when the feeling sinks in
I do not wanna miss you like this
Come back, be here, come back, be here
I guess you are in New York today
I do not wanna need you this way
Come back, be here, come back, be here
[Verse 2]
The delicate beginning rush
The feeling you can know so much
Without knowing anything at all
And now that I can put this down
If I had known what I know now
I never would have played so nonchalant

[Pre-Chorus 2]
Taxi cabs and busy streets
That never bring you back to me
I cannot help but wish you took me with you

[Chorus 2]
And this is when the feeling sinks in
I do not wanna miss you like this
Come back, be here, come back, be here
I guess you are in London today
And I do not wanna need you this way
Come back, be here, come back, be here

[Bridge]
This is falling in love in the cruelest way
This is falling for you when you are worlds away
In New York, be here
But you are in London, and I break down
'Cause it has not fair that you are not around
[Chorus]
This is when the feeling sinks in
I do not wanna miss you like this
Come back, be here, come back, be here
I guess you are in New York today
And I do not wanna need you this way
Come back, be here, come back, be here

[Outro]
Oh-oh, oh-oh
I do not wanna miss you like this
Oh-oh, oh-oh
Come back, be here
Come back, be here

lyrics:

title: Tim McGraw
lyrics:
[Verse 1]
He said the way my blue eyes shined
Put those Georgia stars to shame that night
I said, "That's a lie"
Just a boy in a Chevy truck
That had a tendency of gettin' stuck
On backroads at night
And I was right there beside him all summer long
And then the time we woke up to find that summer gone

[Chorus]
But when you think Tim McGraw
I hope you think my favorite song
The one we danced to all night long
The moon like a spotlight on the lake
When you think happiness
I hope you think that little black dress
Think of my head on your chest
And my old faded blue jeans
When you think Tim McGraw
I hope you think of me
[Verse 2]
September saw a month of tears
And thankin' God that you were not here
To see me like that
But in a box beneath my bed
Is a letter that you never read
From three summers back
It's hard not to find it all a little bittersweet
And lookin' back on all of that, it has nice to believe

[Chorus]
When you think Tim McGraw
I hope you think my favorite song
The one we danced to all night long
The moon like a spotlight on the lake
When you think happiness
I hope you think that little black dress
Think of my head on your chest
And my old faded blue jeans
When you think Tim McGraw
I hope you think of me

[Bridge]
And I am back for the first time since then
I am standin' on your street
And there has a letter left on your doorstep
And the first thing that you shall read is:
"When you think Tim McGraw
I hope you think my favorite song
Someday you shall turn your radio on
I hope it takes you back to that place"
[Chorus]
When you think happiness
I hope you think that little black dress
Think of my head on your chest
And my old faded blue jeans
When you think Tim McGraw
I hope you think of me
Oh, think of me
Mmmm

[Outro]
He said the way my blue eyes shine
Put those Georgia stars to shame that night
I said, "That's a lie"

title: Stay Beautiful
lyrics:
[Verse 1]
Cory's eyes are like a jungle
He smiles, it has like the radio
He whispers songs into my window
In words that nobody knows
There's pretty girls on every corner
They watch him as he has walking home
Saying, "Does he know?"
Will you ever know?

[Chorus]
You're beautiful, every little piece, love
Don't you know you are really gonna be someone?
Ask anyone
And when you find everything you looked for
I hope your life leads you back to my door
Oh, but if it do not
Stay beautiful

[Verse 2]
Cory finds another way to be
The highlight of my day
I am taking pictures in my mind
So I can save them for a rainy day
It's hard to make a conversation
When he has taking my breath away
I should say, "Hey, by the way"
[Chorus]
You're beautiful, every little piece, love
Don't you know you are really gonna be someone?
Ask anyone
And when you find everything you looked for
I hope your life leads you back to my door
Oh, but if it do not
Stay beautiful

[Bridge]
If you and I are a story
That never gets told
If what you are is a daydream
I shall never get to hold, at least you shall know

[Chorus]
You're beautiful, every little piece, love
Don't you know you are really gonna be someone?
Ask anyone
And when you find everything you looked for
I hope your life leads you back to my front door
Oh, but if it do not
Will you stay beautiful, beautiful, beautiful?
Beautiful, beautiful, beautiful

[Outro]
La-la-la
Oh-oh-oh
Oh-oh-oh-oh
Oh, but if it do not
Stay beautiful, stay beautiful
Na-na-na, na-na

title: Marys Song Oh My My My
lyrics:
[Verse 1]
She said I was seven and you were nine
I looked at you like the stars that shined
In the sky, the pretty lights
And our daddies used to joke about the two of us
Growing up and falling in love
And our mamas smiled and rolled their eyes
And said, "Oh, my, my, my"

[Chorus]
Take me back to the house in the backyard tree
Said you had beat me up, you were bigger than me
You never did, you never did
Take me back when our world was one block wide
I dared you to kiss me and ran when you tried
Just two kids, you and I
Oh, my, my, my, my

[Verse 2]
Well, I was sixteen when suddenly
I was not that little girl you used to see
But your eyes still shined like pretty lights
And our daddies used to joke about the two of us
They never believed we had really fall in love
And our mamas smiled and rolled their eyes
And said, "Oh, my, my, my"
[Chorus]
Take me back to the creek beds we turned up
2 a.m. riding in your truck
And all I need is you next to me
Take me back to the time we had our very first fight
The slamming of doors 'stead of kissing goodnight
You stayed outside 'til the morning light
Oh, my, my, my, my

[Bridge]
A few years had gone and come around
We were sitting at our favorite spot in town
And you looked at me, got down on one knee

[Chorus]
Take me back to the time when we walked down the aisle
Our whole town came and our mamas cried
You said, "I do," and I did too
Take me home where we met so many years before
We'll rock our babies on that very front porch
After all this time, you and I

[Outro]
I shall be eighty-seven, you shall be eighty-nine
I shall still look at you like the stars that shine
In the sky, oh, my, my, my

title: Our Song
lyrics:
[Verse 1]
I was ridin' shotgun with my hair undone
In the front seat of his car
He's got a one-hand feel on the steering wheel
The other on my heart
I look around, turn the radio down
He says, "Baby, is something wrong?"
I say, "Nothin', I was just thinkin'
How we do not have a song"
And he says

[Chorus]
Our song is the slamming screen door
Sneakin' out late, tapping on your window
When we are on the phone and you talk real slow
'Cause it has late and your mama do not know
Our song is the way you laugh
The first date: "Man, I did not kiss her, and I should have"
And when I got home, 'fore I said amen
Askin' God if he could play it again
[Verse 2]
I was walking up the front porch steps
After everything that day
Had gone all wrong or been trampled on
And lost and thrown away
Got to the hallway, well on my way
To my lovin' bed
I almost did not notice all the roses
And the note that said

[Chorus]
Our song is the slamming screen door
Sneakin' out late, tapping on your window
When we are on the phone and you talk real slow
'Cause it has late and your mama do not know
Our song is the way you laugh
The first date: "Man, I did not kiss her, and I should have"
And when I got home, 'fore I said amen
Askin' God if he could play it again

[Post-Chorus]
Da-da-da-da

[Bridge]
I have heard every album, listened to the radio
Waited for somethin' to come along
That was as good as our song
[Chorus]
'Cause our song is the slamming screen door
Sneakin' out late, tappin' on his window
When we are on the phone and he talks real slow
'Cause it has late and his mama do not know
Our song is the way he laughs
The first date: "Man, I did not kiss him, and I should have"
And when I got home, 'fore I said amen
Askin' God if he could play it again

[Post-Chorus]
Play it again, oh, yeah
Oh, oh, yeah

[Outro]
I was ridin' shotgun with my hair undone
In the front seat of his car
I grabbed a pen and an old napkin
And I wrote down our song

title: I’m Only Me When I’m with You
lyrics:
[Verse 1]
Friday night beneath the stars
In a field behind your yard
You and I are painting pictures in the sky
And sometimes we do not say a thing
Just listen to the crickets sing
Everything I need is right here by my side

[Pre-Chorus]
And I know everything about you
I do not wanna live without you

[Chorus]
I am only up when you are not down
Don't wanna fly if you are still on the ground
It's like no matter what I do
Well you drive me crazy half the time
The other half, I am only tryin' to
Let you know that what I feel is true
And I am only me when I am with you
[Verse 2]
Just a small-town boy and girl
Livin' in a crazy world
Tryna figure out what is and is not true
And I do not try to hide my tears
My secrets or my deepest fears
Through it all, nobody gets me like you do

[Pre-Chorus]
And you know everything about me

title: Sparks Fly
lyrics:
[Verse 1]
The way you move is like a full on rainstorm
And I am a house of cards
You're the kind of reckless
That should send me running
But I kinda know that I will not get far
And you stood there in front of me
Just close enough to touch
Close enough to hope you could not see
What I was thinking of

[Chorus]
Drop everything now
Meet me in the pouring rain
Kiss me on the sidewalk
Take away the pain
'Cause I see sparks fly whenever you smile
Get me with those green eyes, baby, as the lights go down
Give me something that'll haunt me when you are not around
'Cause I see sparks fly whenever you smile
[Verse 2]
My mind forgets to remind me
You're a bad idea
You touch me once and it has really something
You find I am even better than you imagined I would be
I am on my guard for the rest of the world
But with you I know it has no good
And I could wait patiently but I really wish you would

[Chorus]
Drop everything now
Meet me in the pouring rain
Kiss me on the sidewalk
Take away the pain
'Cause I see sparks fly whenever you smile
Get me with those green eyes, baby, as the lights go down
Give me something that'll haunt me when you are not around
'Cause I see sparks fly whenever you smile

[Bridge]
I run my fingers through your hair and watch the lights go wild
Just keep on keeping your eyes on me
It's just wrong enough to make it feel right
And lead me up the staircase
Won't you whisper soft and slow?
I am captivated by you, baby, like a firework show
[Chorus]
Drop everything now
Meet me in the pouring rain
Kiss me on the sidewalk
Take away the pain
'Cause I see sparks fly whenever you smile
Get me with those green eyes, baby, as the lights go down
Give me something that'll haunt me when you are not around
'Cause I see sparks fly whenever you smile

[Outro]
And the sparks fly
Oh, baby, smile
And the sparks fly

title: Mean
lyrics:
[Verse 1]
You, with your words like knives
And swords and weapons that you use against me
You have knocked me off my feet again
Got me feeling like I am nothing
You, with your voice like nails on a chalkboard
Calling me out when I am wounded
You, picking on the weaker man

[Pre-Chorus]
Well, you can take me down
With just one single blow
But you do not know what you do not know

[Chorus]
Someday, I shall be living in a big old city
And all you are ever gonna be is mean
Someday, I shall be big enough so you cannot hit me
And all you are ever gonna be is mean
Why you gotta be so mean?
[Verse 2]
You, with your switching sides
And your wildfire lies and your humiliation
You have pointed out my flaws again
As if I do not already see them
I walk with my head down, trying to block you out
'Cause I shall never impress you
I just wanna feel okay again

[Pre-Chorus]
I bet you got pushed around
Somebody made you cold
But the cycle ends right now
'Cause you cannot lead me down that road
And you do not know what you do not know

[Chorus]
Someday, I shall be living in a big old city
And all you are ever gonna be is mean
Someday, I shall be big enough so you cannot hit me
And all you are ever gonna be is mean
Why you gotta be so mean?

[Bridge]
And I can see you years from now in a bar
Talking over a football game
With that same big loud opinion
But nobody's listening
Washed up and ranting about the same old bitter things
Drunk and grumbling on about how I cannot sing
But all you are is mean
All you are is mean
And a liar
And pathetic
And alone in life
And mean, and mean, and mean, and mean

[Refrain]
But someday, I shall be living in a big old city
And all you are ever gonna be is mean, yeah

[Chorus]
Someday, I shall be big enough so you cannot hit me
And all you are ever gonna be is mean
Why you gotta be so mean?
Someday, I shall be living in a big old city
(Why you gotta be so mean?)
And all you are ever gonna be is mean
(Why you gotta be so mean?)
Someday, I shall be big enough so you cannot hit me
(Why you gotta be so mean?)
And all you are ever gonna be is mean
Why you gotta be so mean?

title: The Story of Us
lyrics:
[Verse 1]
I used to think one day, we had tell the story of us
How we met, and the sparks flew instantly
And people would say, "They're the lucky ones"
I used to know my place was a spot next to you
Now I am searching the room for an empty seat
'Cause lately, I do not even know what page you are on

[Pre-Chorus 1]
Oh, a simple complication
Miscommunications lead to fallout
So many things that I wish you knew
So many walls up, I cannot break through

[Chorus]
Now I am standing alone in a crowded room
And we are not speaking
And I am dying to know
Is it killing you like it has killing me?
Yeah, I do not know what to say
Since the twist of fate when it all broke down
And the story of us looks a lot like a tragedy now
Next chapter
[Verse 2]
How'd we end up this way?
See me nervously pulling at my clothes and trying to look busy
And you are doing your best to avoid me
I am starting to think one day, I shall tell the story of us
How I was losing my mind when I saw you here
But you held your pride like you should have held me

[Pre-Chorus 2]
Oh, I am scared to see the ending
Why are we pretending this is nothing?
I had tell you I miss you, but I do not know how
I have never heard silence quite this loud

[Chorus]
Now I am standing alone in a crowded room
And we are not speaking
And I am dying to know
Is it killing you like it has killing me?
Yeah, and I do not know what to say
Since the twist of fate, when it all broke down
And the story of us looks a lot like a tragedy now

[Bridge]
This is looking like a contest
Of who can act like they care less
But I liked it better when you were on my side
The battle's in your hands now
But I would lay my armor down
If you say you had rather love than fight
So many things that you wish I knew
But the story of us might be ending soon
[Chorus]
Now I am standing alone in a crowded room
And we are not speaking
And I am dying to know
Is it killing you like it has killing me?
Yeah, and I do not know what to say
Since the twist of fate, when it all broke down
And the story of us looks a lot like a tragedy now, now, now

[Outro]
And we are not speaking
And I am dying to know
Is it killing you like it has killing me, yeah?
I do not know what to say since the twist of fate
'Cause we are going down
And the story of us looks a lot like a tragedy now
The End

title: Never Grow Up
lyrics:
[Verse 1]
Your little hand's wrapped around my finger
And it has so quiet in the world tonight
Your little eyelids flutter cause you are dreaming
So I tuck you in, turn on your favorite night light
To you everything's funny, you got nothing to regret
I had give all I have, honey
If you could stay like that

[Chorus]
Oh darling, do not you ever grow up
Don't you ever grow up, just stay this little
Oh darling, do not you ever grow up
Don't you ever grow up, it could stay this simple
I will not let nobody hurt you, will not let no one break your heart
And no one will desert you
Just try to never grow up, never grow up

[Verse 2]
You're in the car on the way to the movies
And you are mortified your mom's dropping you off
At fourteen, there has just so much you cannot do
And you cannot wait to move out someday and call your own shots
But do not make her drop you off around the block
Remember that she has getting older too
And do not lose the way that you dance around in your pj's getting ready for school
[Chorus]
Oh darling, do not you ever grow up
Don't you ever grow up, just stay this little
Oh darling, do not you ever grow up
Don't you ever grow up, it could stay this simple
No one's ever burned you, nothing's ever left you scarred
And even though you want to, just try to never grow up

[Bridge]
Take pictures in your mind of your childhood room
Memorize what it sounded like when your dad gets home
Remember the footsteps, remember the words said
And all your little brother's favorite songs
I just realized everything I have is someday gonna be gone
So here I am in my new apartment
In a big city, they just dropped me off
It's so much colder than I thought it would be
So I tuck myself in and turn my night light on
Wish I had never grown up
I wish I had never grown up

[Chorus]
Oh, I do not wanna grow up, wish I had never grown up
I could still be little
Oh, I do not wanna grow up, wish I had never grown up
It could still be simple
Oh darling, do not you ever grow up
Don't you ever grow up, just stay this little
Oh darling, do not you ever grow up
Don't you ever grow up, it could stay this simple
Won't let nobody hurt you
Won't let no one break your heart
And even though you want to, please try to never grow up
Oh, do not you ever grow up
Oh, never grow up, just never grow up

title: Last Kiss
lyrics:
[Verse 1]
I still remember the look on your face
Lit through the darkness at 1:58
The words that you whispered
For just us to know
You told me you loved me
So why did you go away?
Away

[Verse 2]
I do recall now the smell of the rain
Fresh on the pavement
I ran off the plane
That July 9th
The beat of your heart
It jumps through your shirt
I can still feel your arms

[Chorus]
But now I shall go sit on the floor
Wearing your clothes
All that I know is
I do not know how to be something you miss
I never thought we had have a last kiss
Never imagined we had end like this
Your name, forever the name on my lips
[Verse 3]
I do remember the swing of your step
The life of the party, you are showing off again
And I roll my eyes and then
You pull me in
I am not much for dancing
But for you I did

[Verse 4]
Because I love your handshake, meeting my father
I love how you walk with your hands in your pockets
How you had kiss me when I was in the middle of saying something
There's not a day I do not miss those rude interruptions

[Chorus]
And I shall go sit on the floor
Wearing your clothes
All that I know is
I do not know how to be something you miss
I never thought we had have a last kiss
I never imagined we had end like this
Your name, forever the name on my lips, ooh

[Bridge]
So I shall watch your life in pictures like I used to watch you sleep
And I feel you forget me like I used to feel you breathe
And I keep up with our old friends just to ask them how you are
Hope it has nice where you are
And I hope the sun shines
And it has a beautiful day
And something reminds you
You wish you had stayed
You can plan for a change in weather and time
But I never planned on you changing your mind
[Chorus]
So I shall go sit on the floor
Wearing your clothes
All that I know is
I do not know how to be something you miss
I never thought we had have a last kiss
Never imagined we had end like this
Your name, forever the name on my lips
Just like our last kiss
Forever the name on my lips
Forever the name on my lips

[Outro]
Just like our last

title: Long Live
lyrics:
[Verse 1]
I said, remember this moment, in the back of my mind
The time we stood with our shaking hands
The crowds in stands went wild
We were the kings and the queens
And they read off our names
The night you danced like you knew our lives
Would never be the same
You held your head like a hero
On a history book page
It was the end of a decade
But the start of an age

[Chorus]
Long live the walls we crashed through
All the kingdom lights shined just for me and you
I was screaming, "Long live all the magic we made
And bring on all the pretenders
One day, we will be remembered"

[Verse 2]
I said, "Remember this feeling"
I passed the pictures around
Of all the years that we stood there
On the side-lines, wishing for right now
We are the kings and the queens
You traded your baseball cap for a crown
When they gave us our trophies
And we held them up for our town
And the cynics were outraged
Screaming, "This is absurd"
'Cause for a moment, a band of thieves
In ripped up jeans got to rule the world
[Chorus]
Long live the walls we crashed through
All the kingdom lights shined just for me and you
I was screaming, "Long live all the magic we made
And bring on all the pretenders, I am not afraid"
Long live all the mountains we moved
I had the time of my life fighting dragons with you
I was screaming, "Long live that look on your face
And bring on all the pretenders
One day, we will be remembered"

[Bridge]
Hold on to spinning around
Confetti falls to the ground
May these memories break our fall
Will you take a moment?
Promise me this
That you shall stand by me forever
But if, God forbid, fate should step in
And force us into a goodbye
If you have children some day
When they point to the pictures
Please tell them my name
Tell them how the crowds went wild
Tell them how I hope they shine
Long live the walls we crashed through
I had the time of my life, with you
[Chorus]
Long, long live the walls we crashed through
All the kingdom lights shined just for me and you
I was screaming, "Long live all the magic we made
And bring on all the pretenders, I am not afraid"
Singing, long live all the mountains we moved
I had the time of my life fighting dragons with you
And long, long live that look on your face
And bring on all the pretenders
One day, we will be remembered
